  "local_port": 47640,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How long should a full time SDE at an Amazon interview preparation take, assuming a moderate level of preparation at this point?",
  "response": "The duration of preparation for a full-time Software Development Engineer (SDE) interview at **Amazon** can vary depending on your current skill level, familiarity with Amazon's interview process, and the amount of time you can dedicate daily. Assuming you\u2019re at a **moderate level of preparation**, here\u2019s a suggested timeline:\n\n---\n\n### **Preparation Duration: 6\u20138 Weeks**\nThis is a reasonable timeframe to prepare thoroughly while balancing other commitments.\n\n---\n\n### **Weekly Breakdown**\n1. **Week 1\u20132: Foundation Building**\n   - Review **data structures** (arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues, trees, graphs, etc.).\n   - Practice **basic algorithms** (sorting, searching, recursion, etc.).\n   - Brush up on **time and space complexity analysis** (Big-O notation).\n   - Start solving **LeetCode Easy** problems to build confidence.\n\n2. **Week 3\u20134: Problem-Solving Practice**\n   - Focus on **LeetCode Medium** problems, especially those tagged with **Amazon**.\n   - Practice **Amazon Leadership Principles** and behavioral questions (prepare **STAR method** responses).\n   - Start working on **system design** fundamentals (if applicable for your level).\n\n3. **Week 5\u20136: Mock Interviews & Advanced Topics**\n   - Solve **LeetCode Hard** problems, focusing on Amazon-favored topics (e.g., trees, graphs, dynamic programming).\n   - Conduct **mock interviews** with peers or use platforms like **Pramp** or **Interviewing.io**.\n   - Deepen your understanding of **system design** (for mid-level or senior roles).\n\n4. **Week 7\u20138: Final Review & Polish**\n   - Revisit challenging problems and areas of weakness.\n   - Practice **timed coding sessions** to simulate real interview conditions.\n   - Refine your behavioral responses and ensure they align with Amazon\u2019s **Leadership Principles**.\n   - Rest and stay confident!\n\n---\n\n### **Daily Time Commitment**\n- If you\u2019re working full-time, aim for **2\u20133 hours on weekdays** and **4\u20136 hours on weekends**.\n- If you can dedicate more time, you may compress the timeline to **4\u20136 weeks**.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Areas to Focus On**\n1. **Coding**: Practice 150\u2013200 problems on LeetCode, with emphasis on Amazon-favored topics.\n2. **Behavioral**: Prepare 5\u201310 strong STAR-based stories for Leadership Principles.\n3. **System Design** (if applicable): Study scalability, microservices, databases, caching, etc.\n4. **Mock Interviews**: Simulate real interview conditions to build confidence.\n\n---\n\n### **Amazon-Specific Tips**\n- Frequent topics: Trees/Graphs, Dynamic Programming, Sliding Window, Two Pointers, HashMaps.\n- Use the **Amazon tagged questions** on LeetCode.\n- Practice explaining your thought process clearly and concisely.\n\n---\n\nBy following this plan, you\u2019ll be well-prepared to tackle Amazon\u2019s SDE interview!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
